@node UPDATE_HISTORY "Offline Orbit Update History - [1] Introduction"
This document describes the changes in Offline Orbit since version 0.80.
History.lha contains older update histories. The first public version of
Offline Orbit (0.02) was released on July 11, 1993.
@endnode
@node OO-0.82 "Offline Orbit Update History - Release 0.82 (March 8, 1997)"
@{b}Announcements: @{ub}

o Epsilon Indi, the support BBS, is no longer in operation. All
  registration keyfiles will be sent out on floppies.

@{b}New features: @{ub}

o All names in message headers are now automatically recapitalized by
  Offline Orbit. This will fix the problems people have been having with
  PCB-OMEN and scandinavian characters (eg. in MBnet).

o Messages can now be sorted by their numbers (see Message Threading).

@{b}Fixes: @{ub}

o Some menu items were ghosted when they shouldn't have been and
  viceversa. Fixed.

o The message header wasn't properly updated after writing a message in the
  Replies Area. Fixed.

o Resizing the puzzle many times easily caused an stack overflow due to the
  recursive nature of the function. Fixed.

o OMEN reply headers contained some inaccurate data that sometimes posted
  messages to wrong areas. Fixed. 
@endnode
@node OO-0.81 "Offline Orbit Update History - Release 0.81 (May 5, 1996)"
@{b}Announcements: @{ub}

o Apologies for the long time it took for this minor update to get
  released. The author has been busy with his studies and other work. He
  has every intention of developing Offline Orbit further.

o Finnish users can now pay registrations directly to the authors bank
  account.

o If you use localization, remember to update the catalogs!

@{b}New features: @{ub}

o OMEN: Offline Orbit now supports the extensions in OMEN revision I.

o OMEN: Offline commands for moderating messages (moving, deleting, etc.)
  are now supported.

o OMEN: Point addresses are now removed from netmail messages before
  they are packed. OMEN doesn't support points.

o "%d" in the packing command is now properly replaced with file names
  instead of using a wildcard (#?) that causes headache for certain packers
  (eg. old ZIP archivers).

o Delete Message and Move Message in Messages menu.

o Expert User in General Preferences.

o New advanced options for editing replies.

o Extra spaces after BBS and sysop names are now removed.

o When opening a new bundle while one is already open, you have the option
  to start a new session for the second bundle.

o Clicking the middle mouse button (if your mouse has one) on the Offline
  Orbit window now opens the area selector (or the Open Bundle requester if
  no bundle is open).

@{b}Fixes: @{ub}

o Control Panel keyboard equivalents didn't always work. Fixed.

o OMEN: Private flag of private messages wasn't saved. Fixed.

o The internal file copying routine didn't free it's memory on pre-3.0
  machines causing severe memory loss. Fixed.

o Some messages were accidentally shown as addressed to "Shell". Fixed.

o A few fixes in the documentation.
@endnode
@node OO-0.80a "Offline Orbit Update History - Release 0.80a (November 12, 1995)"
@{b}Announcements: @{ub}

o Visit Offline Orbit's home page at http://www.mikrobitti.fi/~siren/oo/

@{b}New features: @{ub}

o Number of the message for which the currently displayed message is a
  reply is now shown in brackets in the Number gadget.

o New character conversion option ("-") for disabling the conversion.

o Shell window's title is now localized.

o Used language is now displayed in the About window.

@{b}Fixes: @{ub}

o Window Settings' Mode gadget's titles weren't localized. Fixed. 

o Packer Preferences' Stack gadget's value wasn't saved. Fixed.
@endnode
@node OO-0.80 "Offline Orbit Update History - Release 0.80 (September 16, 1995)"
@{b}Announcements: @{ub}

o Offline Orbit is now shareware. After an evaluation period of twenty
  days you must either register Offline Orbit or discontinue using it. You
  may naturally continue using 0.76 free of charge. This is also why the
  version number suddenly skipped three steps - to clearly separate the
  shareware versions from older freeware releases. Hopefully you will find
  the small compensation for the author's efforts acceptable and register.

  Please, see the manual for further information.

o To contact the author via Internet, send e-mail to siren@mikrobitti.fi.
  Don't use any of the old Internet addresses or the old Fidonet address.

@{b}New features: @{ub}

o Listviews can now be scrolled using a joystick. Trigger equals enter.

o When browsing messages using a joystick, pressing trigger will now open
  the area selector.

o Steal Tag Lines in Messages Menu. it allows you to "steal" tag lines from
  messages.

o You can now use the arrows, Pg Up, Pd Dn, Home and End keys on the
  numeric keypad to browse messages.

o When reading a message, pressing Alt and either one of the vertical arrow
  keys now moves to the beginning (or end) of the message.

o You can now open a bundle by entering it's file name (with full path) as
  a command line parameter when starting Offline Orbit.

o Case Sensitive checkbox in Search window.

o Better error checking for packing replies. If appending fails or the
  packer fails without returning an error code, no replies are destroyed.

o Localization. Description file, as well as translation files for Finnish,
  can be found in the Catalogs directory.

o Quote Header gadget in BBS Preferences.

@{b}Fixes: @{ub}

o OMEN: Message status was by default set to private in areas where both
  public and private messages could be written. Fixed.

o Blue Wave: Offline Orbit had troubles opening bundles from systems that
  use 8 characters long identifiers. Fixed.

o There was a scroll bug in the new listview routines. Fixed.

o Selecting names from the Select User Name list didn't always work
  properly. Fixed.

o Keyboard equivalents of From and To button gadgets in Edit Message window
  weren't disabled when there was no entries in the User List. Fixed.

o Address gadget in Edit Message window was sometimes enabled or disabled
  without a valid reason. Fixed.

o Blue Wave and OMEN: Fixed a bug in packing replies that, among other
  things, caused incorrect netmail addresses to be saved in reply headers.

o Listviews in BBS Preferences, Packer Preferences and User List
  unnecessarily displayed the currently selected item. Fixed.

o Saving message pointers failed if BBS's name contained non-printable
  characters. Fixed.

@{b}Miscellaneous: @{ub}

o Revised brag line.

o Icons for the Icons directory and it's contents.

o Revised icons in the Icons directory.
@endnode
